			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While I do not agree with the merge warder ability, I do like the illusion warder spell.  Earlier it was suggested to have effects similar to form of the great wolf plus regen and haste.  While very nice indeed lets take a look at 2 spells which take the forms of an animal.
<br />

<br />
Form of the Great Wolf - Druid lvl 44 Mana 135 Duration 2hrs 24 min
<br />
Effects: 
<br />
Movement rate increase: 57%-60%
<br />
Attack increase: 45-51
<br />
Ultravision
<br />

<br />
Form of the Great Bear - Shaman lvl 55 Mana 135 Duration 2hrs 24 min
<br />
Effects:
<br />
Regen: 2 per tick
<br />
Wisdom: +10 
<br />

<br />
Now I think it is a bad idea to give each illusion warder a different effect purely because no other beastlord spells are race specific.  (Although I do believe that EQ should have been designed to be that way for a number of classes and races in the first place-but that is neither here nor there)
<br />

<br />
Also I believe that the illusion should mirror the actual warder's abilities a bit more.  Now the only ability the pet pretty much naturally has is a regen rate while not moving.  For arguments sake lets surmise that warder's have ultravision as well.
<br />

<br />
For other abilities I think we should turn to the pet buff line.  Lets look at the lower one:
<br />

<br />
Yekan's Quickening - Beastlord lvl 39 Mana 200 duration 15 min
<br />
Effects:
<br />
Haste: 60%
<br />
Strength increase: 44-45
<br />
AC: 12
<br />
Attack: 20
<br />

<br />
Now I will attempt to combin the aforementioned abilities and the buff effects in a way that is balanced:
<br />

<br />
Illusion Warder - Beastlord lvl 59 Mana 300 duration 2hrs 24 min
<br />
Effects: - all self only
<br />
Illusion: warder type per race
<br />
Haste: 30% (stackable with other haste spells)
<br />
Regen: 2 per tick (stackable with other regen spells)
<br />
Attack: 20 (stackable with certain other attack buff spells)
<br />
Ultravision
<br />
(replaced ac for regen.  Lowered haste amount.  Replaced str with ultravision.  Gave no movement rate increase and no wisdom boost)
<br />

<br />
A pretty nice spell I think  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=385013" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kammen</a>
<br />
New Outriders
<br />
The Rathe
<br />

<br />
Everyman dies, not every man truly lives.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
