			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One trouble with the concept is that Beastlords get self, group, and targetable buffs that are difficult to surpass.  
<br />

<br />
For instance, we get 15 pt/tick regen + Spritual Domain for a grand total of 24 HP/tick!  Soloing shamans can only dream of this without investing in a fungi
<br />
Also, we get the best resistance buffs in the game, +65 to all resists.
<br />

<br />
We also get 50% targetable haste, 65% slow, the best ATK buffs in the game.. what could an illusion offer that our buffs cannot?
<br />

<br />
My thought is for an alteration of an exsisting spell:  Frenzy.
<br />

<br />
This is lvl 49, adds a good chunk to DEX, AGI, STR, and AC and limits casting for about 30 sconds.  It also lasts for about 15 minutes making it a must for fighting situations.  
<br />

<br />
What ought to be done is to simply add an illusion to this, make no other changes excepting maybe change it into a 2 minute duration during which spells cannot be cast at all, though that's optional.  
<br />

<br />
My concerns with this is that there are no race specific spells that do certain things to certain races (Excepting maybe shrink, which doesn't affect gnomes and maybe halflings and dwarfs), so having the illusion be the same as your pet might be out... nor can I think of something that would fit all 5 races well as being their 'frenzed state'
<br />

<br />
Quite likely it's a programing issue.. that being that it's too much programing for little change to the game mechanics.<br />_________________<br /><IMG SRC="http://myweb.cableone.net/pojodan/KitchiSig2.jpg">
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543215" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543215</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
